'''Piotr Morawski''' (December 27, 1976 – April 8, 2009) was a Polish [[mountaineer]]. He was best known for making the first successful winter ascent together with [[Simone Moro]] of [[Shishapangma]] on January 14, 2005. Morawski died aged 32 during an international [[Dhaulagiri]]/[[Manaslu]] expedition in [[Nepal]]. He fell into a [[crevasse]] at an elevation of 5500&nbsp;m while acclimatizing.
